(self.webpackChunkvuepress2=self.webpackChunkvuepress2||[]).push([[511],{5221:(e,t,r)=>{"use strict";r.r(t),r.d(t,{data:()=>a});const a={key:"v-05e2fbac",path:"/bloodflow/Microstructure%20and%20cerebral%20blood%20flow%20changes%20in%20patients%20recovered%20from%20COVID%2019.html",title:"无神经系统表现的 COVID-19 康复患者大脑微结构和脑血流的长期后果",lang:"zh-CN",frontmatter:{},excerpt:"",headers:[{level:2,title:"重点：",slug:"重点",children:[]}],filePathRelative:"bloodflow/Microstructure and cerebral blood flow changes in patients recovered from COVID 19.md",git:{updatedTime:162031299e4,contributors:[]}}},1799:(e,t,r)=>{"use strict";r.r(t),r.d(t,{default:()=>o});const a=(0,r(6252).uE)('<h1 id="无神经系统表现的-covid-19-康复患者大脑微结构和脑血流的长期后果"><a class="header-anchor" href="#无神经系统表现的-covid-19-康复患者大脑微结构和脑血流的长期后果">#</a> 无神经系统表现的 COVID-19 康复患者大脑微结构和脑血流的长期后果</h1><p>Qin Y, Wu J, Chen T, et al. Long-term microstructure and cerebral blood flow changes in patients recovered from COVID-19 without neurological manifestations. <em>J Clin Invest</em>. 2021;131(8):147329.</p><p>doi:10.1172/JCI147329</p><h2 id="重点"><a class="header-anchor" href="#重点">#</a> 重点：</h2><p><img src="https://dm5migu4zj3pb.cloudfront.net/manuscripts/147000/147329/medium/JCI147329.ga.jpg" alt="img"></p><p>COVID-19 对大脑的长期影响。</p><p>出院后3个月差 MRI。</p><p>病情严重的患者，皮质厚度（cortical thickness）便薄，脑血流（CBF）减少，白质（white matter，WM）微结构改变都更严重，尤其是额叶和边缘系统。另外，大脑微结构、脑血流以及白质束参数的改变与炎症标志物 CRP 、PCT 和 IL-6 具有相关性。</p><p>验证风暴的间接损伤可能会损害但看，改变脑容量、脑血流以及白质束（white matter tracts）。COVID-19 相关的缺氧和血管内皮功能障碍可能导致神经改变。恢复期需要监测大脑这些区域的异常，可能会帮助医生了解 COVID-19 可能导致的神经后果。</p><p>pcASL, pseudo-continuous arterial spin labeling 核磁伪连续动脉自旋标记</p>',10),o={render:function(e,t){return a}}}}]);